Bonus Task: AI-Powered Intelligent Code Review Assistant (ICRA)
Innovation Proposal: "ReviewBot-AI"

1. EXECUTIVE SUMMARY
Problem Statement:
Code reviews are critical for quality but consume 20-30% of developer time. Traditional code review processes are:

Time-Intensive: Average 2-4 hours per pull request
Inconsistent: Quality varies by reviewer experience/fatigue
Limited Scope: Human reviewers miss subtle bugs, security vulnerabilities
Bottlenecked: Senior developers become review bottlenecks
Late Detection: Issues found in review should've been caught earlier

Proposed Solution:
ReviewBot-AI - An intelligent AI system that provides real-time, comprehensive code review feedback before human reviewers engage, reducing review time by 60-70% while improving code quality.
Key Innovation:
Unlike existing tools (SonarQube, CodeClimate) that check syntax and static rules, ReviewBot-AI uses:

Large Language Models (LLMs) for semantic code understanding
Knowledge Graphs encoding organizational best practices
Contextual Learning from past review comments
Multi-dimensional Analysis (correctness, security, performance, maintainability, style)

Expected Impact:

60-70% reduction in human review time
40% increase in bug detection before merge
$500K-1M annual savings for 50-developer team
30% faster time-to-production